ENTRY            A0894   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
SUBENT        A0894001   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                 11         33
TITLE      New results on elements 111 and 112
AUTHOR     (S.Hofmann, F.P.Hesberger, D.Ackermann, G.Muenzenberg,
           S.Antalic, P.Cagarda, B.Kindler, J.Kojouharova,
           M.Leino, B.Lommel, R.Mann,  A.G.Popeko, S.Reshitko,
           S.Saro, J.Uusitalo, A.V.Yeremin)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,14,147,2002)
INSTITUTE  (2GERGSI,3SLKUB,2SF JYV,4ZZZDUB)
FACILITY   (LINAC,2GERGSI) The UNILAC accelerator and the
           velocity filter SHIP (Separator for Heavy-Ion reaction
           Products) at GSI.
SAMPLE     The targets were prepared by evaporation of lead or
           bismuth deposited in layers of 450 ug/cm2 on carbon
           backing foils of 40 ug/cm2. The target layers were
           then covered by evaporation of a 10 ug/cm2 thick
           carbon layer to protect the targets from sputtering
           and to enhance radiative cooling. The total thickness
           of these carbon foils amounted to 190 ug/cm2.
DETECTOR   (MAGSP) The evaporated residues (ERs) were
           separated from the beam by the velocity filter SHIP and
           implanted into a position-sensitive strip Si detector
            (focal-plane stop detector)
           (SISD)
           The detector system was completed by a Si veto detector
           and a Ge clover detector, both mounted behind the
           stop detector. The clover detector was separated from
           the SHIP vacuum by a 1mm thick aluminium window.
METHOD     (TOF)
MISC-COL   (MISC) The calculated excitation energy of the
           compound nucleus for reactions in the middle of the
           target thickness.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
HISTORY    (20110816C) SB
           (20260204U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              33
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           36
